    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "t_start": 0.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "narration_text": "She pasted her memo as a format example. Claude returned something perfectly matching the format \u2014 and the casual tone she never meant to include.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "kind": "title",
        "copy": "Why your examples teach more than your instructions",
        "sub": "the features you never meant to copy"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.25,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B01.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "t_start": 9.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "narration_text": "Priya runs communications for a research institute. She needs a formal board report. She pastes a casual internal memo as a format reference and types: write the board report in the same style.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "STILL",
        "source": "ai",
        "motion": "kenburns"
      },
      "scene_description": "A professional woman at her desk, looking at two documents side by side on a laptop screen, newsprint editorial treatment",
      "image_prompt": "B02, professional woman at a modern office desk, two documents visible on laptop screen, focused expression, editorial newsprint treatment, desaturated flat print, collage style",
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.23,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "t_start": 20.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "act": "THE QUESTION",
      "narration_text": "She wanted Claude to copy the paragraph structure. Instead it copied the casual register, hedging language, and short sentence rhythm too. Why did the example teach more than she intended?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "kind": "question",
        "copy": "Why did the example teach more than she intended?",
        "sub": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.76,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 29.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "narration_text": "Instructions in prompts are explicit \u2014 they describe what you want. But an example is an instruction in disguise. It teaches by demonstration across every feature it contains, whether or not you labeled any of them.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B04_InstructionVsExample"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.85,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "t_start": 40.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "narration_text": "A memo has observable features. Structure: topics in paragraphs. Register: casual, hedged. Sentence length: short. Tone: conversational. When you paste it without annotation, all of these carry equal weight as teaching signal.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B05_FeatureDimensions"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 16.9,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "t_start": 52.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Claude pattern-matches across all of them at once. It cannot know which features you consider essential and which are incidental unless you say. So it treats the example as a complete specification \u2014 and learns everything in it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B06_AllFeaturesEqual"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.22,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "t_start": 63.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Structure passes through. But so does register, sentence length, hedging density, and vocabulary. The board report returns sounding like the memo \u2014 because it was taught by the memo.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B07_AllFeaturesCopied"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.65,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "t_start": 73.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Annotation changes this. You tell Claude which features to copy \u2014 and which to ignore. The example stays; the specification narrows it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "kind": "section",
        "copy": "The fix: annotate the example",
        "sub": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.04,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "t_start": 83.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Priya adds three lines to her prompt: copy the paragraph-per-topic structure. Not the casual tone. Not the hedging language. Now only one feature carries signal. The rest are excluded.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B09_AnnotatedExample"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.27,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "t_start": 96.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "narration_text": "This holds for any example \u2014 a quote you liked, a competitor's press release, a paper abstract. Each contains dozens of features. Without annotation, all of them teach.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B10_AnyExample"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.4,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "t_start": 106.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "narration_text": "Marco writes a product blog post. He pastes a competitor's post he admires and asks Claude to match the style. The output is punchy, short-sentenced, and uses three exclamation points \u2014 which were in the competitor's post, which he hates. He never labeled them as features to exclude.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B11_MarcoExample"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 18.99,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B11.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B11.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "t_start": 118.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "narration_text": "He adds one line: copy the punchy short sentences. Not the exclamation points \u2014 we never use those. Next output: punchy, short, zero exclamation points. The example stayed. The annotation narrowed it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B12_MarcoFixed"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 14.94,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B12.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B12.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "t_start": 130.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "act": "THE PRACTICE",
      "narration_text": "The practice: before you paste any example, write two sentences. Which features should Claude copy? Which should it ignore? Those two sentences are your annotation \u2014 and they are the actual specification.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "graphic": {
        "manim": "B13_Practice"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B13.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.14,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B13.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B13.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B14",
      "t_start": 141.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "act": "RECAP",
      "narration_text": "An unannotated example teaches every feature it contains. Label which to copy, which to skip \u2014 and your example becomes a precise instruction instead of a full transfer.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "kind": "endcard",
        "copy": "Unannotated examples teach everything.",
        "sub": "Annotation makes them precise."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B14.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.938,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-examples-teach-more/clips/B14.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-examples-teach-more/mp3/beat-B14.mp3"
    },
